Three sisters aged seven, 10, and 18 died when they were struck by lightning in Mantshilibeni location, Vonqo village, Dutywa, this week, Eastern Cape police said on Saturday. All of them passed away at the scene. It is alleged that the deceased were in a rondavel hut when lightning struck them, Captain Jackson Manatha said. The children s parents were not at home when the incident happened late on Thursday evening. The grandmother of the children was in a separate house and was unharmed. Dutywa police had opened an inquest docket, he said. African News Agency (ANA) DA opposed to ANC referendum on expropriation without compensation